                       <decoDesc>
                           
                         <summary>The illustrations grouped in this volume were first studied by their former
                             owner, Bent Juel-Jensen, who assigned them, with reason, to a period between
                             <date notBefore="1650" notAfter="1750"/> and 
                             attributed them to the so-called <persName ref="PRS12971GroundHornbill" role="illustrator"/>.</summary>
                           
                           <decoNote xml:id="d1" type="miniature">
                               <locus target="#1v"/>
                               <desc>The miniature depicts several members of the Zāgʷe dynasty.
                                   The five standing <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men</ref> 
                                   are identified by captions as:
                              <persName ref="PRS10325Yemreha"/>,
                              <persName ref="PRS6152Lalibala"/>,
                               <persName ref="PRS7437Naakkwe"/>, and
                               <persName ref="PRS5111harbay"/>; 
                                   it is unclear if the last figure represents the Aksumite King
                               <persName ref="PRS4327GabraMa"/> 
                                   since this was also the regal name used by several rulers of the Zāgʷe dynasty.
                                   All five men have a <term key="halo"/> and a <term key="codex"/> in their right hand.
                                   <q xml:lang="gez"> <persName ref="PRS10325Yemreha">ይምርሐነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</persName> 
                                       <persName ref="PRS6152Lalibala">ላሊበላ፡</persName>  <persName ref="PRS7437Naakkwe">ነአኵቶ፡ ለአብ፡ </persName> 
                                       <persName ref="PRS5111harbay">ሃርቤ፡</persName> ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡</q>
                               </desc>
                           </decoNote>
                           
                           <decoNote xml:id="d2" type="miniature">
                               <locus target="#2v"/>
                               <desc>Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men</ref>. 
                                   The one in the centre, in an <term key="gestureorans">orans pose</term>,  is 
                                   <persName ref="PRS4306GabraMa"/>. The two smaller figures at his
                                   side are <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/>, to the right and 
                                   <persName ref="PRS7840Phanuel"/>, to the right.
                                   The <term key="angel">angels</term> hold a <term key="sword"/>; 
                                   all three figures have a <term key="halo"/>.
                                   <q xml:lang="gez"> ሚካኤል 
                                       <gap reason="illegible" unit="chars" extent="2"/>
                                      አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፋኑኤል፡ መልአክ፡</q>
                               </desc>
                           </decoNote>
                    
                        
                        <decoNote xml:id="d3" type="miniature">
                            <locus target="#3r"/>
                            <desc>Five <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men</ref> with
                                <term key="sword">swords</term>, identified, from left to right, as 
                                <persName ref="PRS3126Claudius"/>
                                <persName ref="PRS2548Basilide"/>
                                <persName ref="PRS7025Mercury"/>
                                <persName ref="PRS9470Theodore"/>
                                <persName ref="PRS9744Victor"/> <!-- NOT SURE IF RIGHT VICTOR-->
                                The warrior <term key="saint">saints</term>, who hold a <term key="sword"/> and have a <term key="halo"/>,
                                are unusually not shown on horseback.
                                <q xml:lang="gez">ፋሲለደስ፡ ገላውዴዎስ፡ መርቆ<sic>ራ</sic>ዎስ፡ ቴዎድሮስ፡ ፊቅጦር፡፡</q>  
                            </desc>
                        </decoNote>
                           
                           <decoNote xml:id="d4" type="miniature">
                               <locus target="#4r"/>
                               <desc>The <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>
                                   with the <term key="deadjesus"/> on the 
                                   <term key="cross"/>. <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/>, to the left, is identified by the caption
                                   <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዝእት፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>. 
                                   <persName ref="PRS5695John"/>, to the righ, is identified by the caption 
                                   <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዮሐንስ፡ ረድእ፡</foreign>
                                   <q xml:lang="gez">ፀሐይ፡ ጸልመ፡ ዘተሰቀለ<corr>፡</corr> እግዚእነ፡ ወርኅ፡ ደመ።</q>  
                               </desc>
                           </decoNote>
                        
                        </decoDesc>
                        
